    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i'm working on a bathroom remodel and the drywall seams are looking pretty uneven after the first coat of mud. what's the best way to tape and mud these so i don't end up with visible ridges once i start sanding?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To prevent visible ridges, start by using a fiberglass mesh tape over your joints, making sure it covers the entire seam. Apply a thin layer of setting-type compound directly over the tape, feathering the edges outward to blend it into the existing drywall. After that, apply your first skim coat, ensuring it's smooth and wide enough to completely cover the tape, and allow it to dry thoroughly before moving on.",
      "source": "target",
